                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- The beginning of Text I-1 is written in quire I (added later to the Ms.) and continued on <locus target="#148v">148v</locus> in this same hand a.</note>
                     <note>- The second part of Text I-2 is introduced with the word mǝʿrāf “chapter”.</note>
                     <note>- Only the miracles introduced with the words taʾammǝr “miracle” or täʾamrihu “his miracle” are numbered (42 miracles). Other miracles are introduced with the words nägär “speech” and mǝʿrāf “chapter”. A few miracles have no particular introducing word.</note>
                  </msItem>
